{{Talk | Conference=SMWCon Fall 2012 | Title=Collaborative Financial Analysis using Semantic MediaWiki | Description= Using Semantic MediaWiki for a more agile approach of collaborative budgeting, expense planning, and analysis in a use case of finance management within a research group. | Keywords=finance, pivot analyis, triple store, planning, case study | Duration= 20 minutes | Start=25 Oct 2012 16:40 | End=25 Oct 2012 17:00 | Type=Talk | Audience=Everyone | Speakers=Benedikt Kämpgen, Tobias Zundel | Attendees= | Slides external=http://www.aifb.kit.edu/web/Vortrag3292/en | Video=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kCBzr36evEw }}
Many organisations use Excel for budgeting and expense planning and for comparing budgets and plans with financial outcomes. Great organisations use spreadsheets only for reports and presentations [http://dssresources.com/papers/features/castellina&hatch/CFO_IXN_Shared%20Research_No2_Financial,%20Planning,%20Budgeting%20and%20Forecasting%20in%20the%20New%20Economy_Aberdeen,Mar%202011.pdf], whereas the actual data is stored in server-based systems.
However, for users, those systems are mostly read-only. ETL processes regularly extract, preprocess, and load financial data into a data warehouse. Only interactive analyses can be performed and static reports created, yet, discussions and documentation of actions are done offline, using office suites.
We will discuss how to use Semantic MediaWiki for a more agile approach of collaborative budgeting, expense planning, and analysis in a use case of finance management within a research group.
