"Data is data" and the future of data browsing, Toward a unified theory of data browsing, and what it means for SMW's browsing functionality, including Semantic Drilldown and others. Yaron Koren

{{Talk | Conference=SMWCon Spring 2013 | Title=ArchE: An SMW-based Architecture Repository, | Description=Discussion & demo of ArchE, our enterprise infrastructure architecture repository used to track relationships between architecture definitions, patterns, and building blocks. | Start=21 Mar 2013 16:30 | End=21 Mar 2013 17:00 | Duration=30 minutes | Type=Talk | Audience=Everyone | Slides internal = SMWCon_Spring_2013/ArchE/Presentation | Speakers=Larry Claman | Attendees= | Video=https://vimeo.com/67228192 }}
At Reed Elsevier Technology Services, we've built a repository for our enterprise technology artifacts using SMW technology. We've done some novel work using semantic properties to manage the forward & reverse relationships between the artifacts, including development of a graphical "Knowledge Map".
